doc.previous: These tunnels are used in the studies of noise generated by flow and its suppression
doc.after: The aerodynamic principles of the wind tunnel work equally on watercraft except the water is more viscous and so sets greater forces on the object being tested A looping flume is typically used for underwater aquadynamic testing The interaction between 2 different types of fluids means that pure windtunnel testing is only partly relevant However a similar sort of research is done in a towing tank
